Study Abroad Summer High School Summer in New York City Programs for Visiting Students Open Arts Minors Blog Events Newsletters Videos Admin & Faculty Alumni Contact Us  home > Special Programs        Theatres of the Black Atlantic  THEA-UT 741.  4 Credits Instructor(s): Check Albert Through a close examination of dramatic texts, theatrical groups and movements, this course will offer a comparative study of drama and theatre produced by African, African-American, Black British and Caribbean practitioners. It will explore how conventions of drama and theatre, as cultural practices, offer sites for performing identity and subjectivity. The course will use the idea of the Black Atlantic as a framing device signifying Africa’s historical encounter with Europe, and the connections of Africans and people of African descent in Britain, the USA and the Caribbean. Check Albert for course schedule. Study Abroad Summer High School Summer in New York City Programs for Visiting Students Open Arts Minors Blog Events Newsletters Videos Admin & Faculty Alumni Contact Us  home > Special Programs        Theatres of the Black Atlantic  THEA-UT 741.  4 Credits Instructor(s): Check Albert Through a close examination of dramatic texts, theatrical groups and movements, this course will offer a comparative study of drama and theatre produced by African, African-American, Black British and Caribbean practitioners. It will explore how conventions of drama and theatre, as cultural practices, offer sites for performing identity and subjectivity. The course will use the idea of the Black Atlantic as a framing device signifying Africa’s historical encounter with Europe, and the connections of Africans and people of African descent in Britain, the USA and the Caribbean. Check Albert for course schedule.
